## Context

RDJ-26561 R&R (tracker 0274), remark ED-03. Editor: add a table describing
the variables of `climate_finance_corpus.csv`, placed after the dataset is
described in the main text. The referee's related usability complaint about
the CSV's column layout (R1-19) is arbitrated separately in ticket 0287 —
restructuring the shipped data product is an author decision; the variables
table lands regardless of that outcome.

## Relevant files

- `deliverables/data-paper/data-paper.qmd` — Data section
- `climate_finance_corpus.csv` production script (Phase 1/export) — column
  ground truth; `scripts/schemas.py` if a Pandera schema exists
- `deliverables/_shared/tables/` — where a generated table would land

## Actions

1. Generate the variables table from the CSV/schema itself (Make target +
   script per Phase-2 rules — no hand-curated table), one row per column:
   name, type, description, source.
2. Insert it in data-paper.qmd after the dataset description.

## Test

- Table columns match the actual CSV header (a test comparing generated table
  to the artifact).

## Verification

- [ ] Table regenerates from the pipeline; no drift from the shipped CSV

## Invariants

- No hand-curated data in the pipeline (Make rule).

## Exit criteria

- [ ] Variables table present in data-paper.qmd, generated not hand-written
- [ ] Response-letter bullet drafted (feeds 0283)
